{"title":"Women’s Tour Down Under 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/womens-tour-down-under-preview","date":1704993268000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/womens-tour-down-under-preview\">Women’s Tour Down Under 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know</a></p>\n\n<p>Road racing is back! Whether you’ll be staying up to watch it or not, pro cycling is on the road again starting with the Women’s Tour Down Under, where fans will get to see refreshed riders, new kits and even some <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-2024-red-bull-bora-hansgrohe\" target=\"_blank\">fresh national championship jerseys</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The race, now in its seventh edition with a couple of lost years to Covid, begins on Friday 12th January in Hahndorf and consists of three stages, finishing on Sunday 14th January at Willunga Hill.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last year’s Women’s Tour Down under was won by FDJ-Suez’s Grace Brown over Trek-Segafredo’s Amanda Spratt and EF Education-TIBCO-SVB’s Georgia Williams, and Brown and Spratt will be back to do battle in 2024.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/2024-pro-cycling-kit\">All the 2024 WorldTour kits ranked from worst to first</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/2024-pro-cycling\">6 pro cycling things I’m looking forward to in 2024</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-2024-red-bull-bora-hansgrohe\">Pro Log: Red Bull acquires controlling stake in Bora-Hansgrohe, Australian National Championships results, EF release stunning kits and Julien Vermote signs for Visma-Lease a Bike</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/2024-men-pro-cycling-preview\">5 key storylines for the 2024 men’s pro cycling season</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/2024-women-pro-cycling-preview\">5 key storylines for the 2024 women’s pro cycling season</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Women’s Tour Down Under 2024: Key information</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"776\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-3-776x970.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-3-776x970.jpeg 776w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-3-240x300.jpeg 240w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-3-768x960.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-3-750x938.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-3-1140x1425.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-3.jpeg 1200w\" /><figcaption>Santos Tour Down Under</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dates:</strong> 12th January-14th January</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Start:</strong> Hahndorf, South Australia</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Finish:</strong> Willunga Hill, South Australia</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Stages:</strong> Three</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Television coverage:</strong> Eurosport, Discovery+, Seven Network</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>2023 winner:</strong> Grace Brown (FDJ-Suez)</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Most wins:</strong> Amanda Spratt (three)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Women’s Tour Down Under 2024 route</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"830\" height=\"765\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-route.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-route.png 830w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-route-300x277.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-route-768x708.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-route-750x691.png 750w\" /><figcaption>Santos Tour Down Under</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>The Women’s Tour Down Under sticks mainly to the Adelaide area in South Australia, so many of the locations in the 2024 edition will be familiar to previous viewers of both the women’s and men’s race.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Women’s Tour Down Under 2024: Stage-by-stage preview</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Friday 12th January, Hahndorf – Campbelltown, 93.9km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"261\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-1-profile-970x261.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-1-profile-970x261.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-1-profile-300x81.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-1-profile-768x207.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-1-profile-1536x414.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-1-profile-2048x552.png 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-1-profile-750x202.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-1-profile-1140x307.png 1140w\" /><figcaption>Santos Tour Down Under</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Two short climbs get the blood pumping on Stage 1 before a probable sprint finish in Campbelltown to decide the first leader.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Saturday 13th January, Glenelg – Stirling, 104.2km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"263\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-2-profile-970x263.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-2-profile-970x263.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-2-profile-300x81.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-2-profile-768x208.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-2-profile-1536x416.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-2-profile-2048x555.png 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-2-profile-750x203.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-2-profile-1140x309.png 1140w\" /><figcaption>Santos Tour Down Under</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Stage 2 gets a bit tougher with a hard climb shortly after the start with a max gradient of 15.6%, once the peloton gets to Stirling they start the circuit, which will be done twice and finishes with a climb that’ll be sure to shake things up. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Sunday 14th January, Adelaide – Willunga Hill, 93.4km</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"262\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-3-profile-970x262.png\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-3-profile-970x262.png 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-3-profile-300x81.png 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-3-profile-768x207.png 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-3-profile-1536x415.png 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-3-profile-2048x553.png 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-3-profile-750x203.png 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2024-stage-3-profile-1140x308.png 1140w\" /><figcaption>Santos Tour Down Under</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It should all come down to this one though, with the famous Willunga Hill waiting to crown the 2024 winner of the Women’s Tour Down Under.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Women’s Tour Down Under 2024: Live TV and streaming guide</h2>\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"776\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2023-1-776x970.jpeg\" alt=\"Grace Brown raises arms aloft in celebration, beating Amanda Spratt behind\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2023-1-776x970.jpeg 776w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2023-1-240x300.jpeg 240w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2023-1-768x960.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2023-1-750x938.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2023-1-1140x1425.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/01/womens-tour-down-under-2023-1.jpeg 1200w\" /><figcaption>Santos Tour Down Under</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>GCN+ may be gone, but the Women’s Tour Down Under will be available to watch in the UK on Eurosport and Discovery+. <a href=\"https://auth.discoveryplus.com/gb/product?flow=purchase&amp;videoAssetId=6021174\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a> costs £6.99 for the more basic package, which includes cycling and all the other Eurosport programmes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In Australia you can catch the action on 7plus and 7mate. In New Zealand it’s being shown on Sky.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Elsewhere coverage will be on SuperSport in Africa; NBC in the United States; FloBikes in the US and Canada; Eurosport, J Sports (Japan) and Zhibo (China) in Asia Pacific and Oceania; Eurosport, L’Équipe (France), TV2 (Denmark) and rtve (Spain) in Europe; ESPN in Latin America; and Abu Dhabi Sport TV in the Middle East.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If it’s not being shown in your country you may be able to watch coverage using a VPN – Virtual Private Network – which allows users to mask their IP address and watch geo-blocked content, provided they don’t need to pay for a subscription. This is also helpful for watching paid-for coverage while travelling abroad in countries without access. One such example is <a href=\"https://go.expressvpn.com/m5yJGZ\" target=\"_blank\">ExpressVPN</a>, which is very <a href=\"https://www.independent.co.uk/advisor/vpn/expressvpn-review\" target=\"_blank\">well reviewed</a>, helps users to find way to watch cycling without having to pay for broadcasters services, and costs £5.36 per month with three-months free. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul></ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Women’s Tour Down Under 2024: TV and streaming times</h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 1: Friday 12th January</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Eurosport and Discovery+: </strong>00:30-4:00 GMT<br /><strong>7plus and 7mate: </strong>11:00-14:30 ACDT</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 2: Saturday 13th January</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Eurosport and Discovery+: </strong>00:30-4:30 GMT<br /><strong>7plus and 7mate: </strong>11:00-15:00 ACDT</p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Stage 3: Sunday 14th January</h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Eurosport and Discovery+: </strong>00:30-4:00 GMT<br /><strong>7plus and 7mate: </strong>11:00-15:00 ACDT</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Women’s Tour Down Under 2024 start list</h2>\n\n\n\n<div><p><em>Data powered by <a href=\"https://firstcycling.com/race.php?r=9080&amp;y=2024&amp;k=8\" target=\"_blank\">FirstCycling.com</a></em></p></div>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/womens-tour-down-under-preview\">Women’s Tour Down Under 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Will Strickson &#124; Deputy Website Editor","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"adaa964a604115661c298f8353ed43a34d52430d463dbbd0180dba4f0c822c4b","category":"Cycling"}